Database: 


users have many Items (inventory)
users have many orders
users table: 
- id
- name
- email
- ... 

<!-- items (inventory) have many users -->
inventory table: contains the of all the items in the store.. 
- id
- item_name 
- serial_number: asdfasf23423dasdf (random hash)
- quantity 
- price 
- category: art, music... (enum)
- ...
- updated_at
- created_at

orders belong to users (one to many)
orders have many order Items
orders table: 
- id
- user_id
- order_items: list of purchased items..
- total price/ or cost 
- date of purchase 
- ...

<!-- itemsOrdered belong to orders (one to many) -->
itemsOrdered table?
- id
- user_id
- order_id 
- inventory_id
- quantity
- anything else you need...


row in orders table : 1, 2, 10, 100, 1/1/2022
order_items: 
2, 1, 1, ....
2, 1, 2, ....
2, 1, 3, ....




